Full Description: SlopeViews provides complete immersive video production services.  From concept development to final dissemination, the company works closely with clients to create a custom 360º video experience.  SlopeViews also integrates 360º immersive videos into trail maps, village maps, or building floorplans. Concept Development — The unique nature of spherical video requires innovative thinking and fresh ideas for each project.  During concept development, they work to develop a unique approach to 360º video.   Custom Collection — The camera crews can operate over any terrain on foot, on skis, or from any type of vehicle.  They will implement a plan to capture exactly what is needed to create a project that will deliver.  Post Production — In the studio, they will write a custom stitching script that will ensure the video is seamless, then process the eleven video streams into a single hi-resolution file that is edited and manipulated to suit the clients need. Editing — This is where they will cut, make adjustments for color and light, and insert additional audio or visual effects to create the conceptualized immersive video.   Dissemination — They will  integrate the immersive application into any website.  This includes installation of the Flash Player, ensuring existing server support, libraries, extensions, and testing.  Web hosting and web streaming are available, as well as CD, DVD or hard drive distribution. The services can help empower the client's customers and engage new visitors with rich, interactive 3D video.  The company helps strengthen web presence and enhance advertising with location-based services, floating video ads, and the integration of meta-data with augmented reality into the video.   - Build interactive, immersive maps of ski, golf, or resort destinations. - Showcase facilities and venues with full motion immersive tours. - Create powerful sales tools for reservations and vacation bookings. - Document extreme sporting events and musical concerts. - Enhance situational and spatial awareness of any environment. - Streamline planning and design operations. - Archive data for future use.

Description: Vrtii is a mobile advertising system that lets users win real-life prizes by playing simple, engaging, fun smartphone games.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Vrtii is a mobile advertising system that lets users win real-life prizes by playing simple, engaging, fun smartphone games just like the ones they already play. Unlike most digital advertising platforms today, where content is in one place and advertisements in another, on Vrtii, the advertisement is the content. When users come to Vrtii, they come specifically to play games that will win them coupons and promotions from the brands they are already interested in connecting with. Vrtii is a true win-win solution, offering value to players and advertisers alike: For players, Vrtii is a fun, easy, engaging way to turn virtual-world gaming into real-world rewards. For advertisers, Vrtii is a low-expense, high-rewards approach to creating the kinds of interactions that turn into meaningful, lasting customer relationships. How it works: The Vrtii experience starts with the user: users come to the Vrtii app on their smartphone, play a fun, entertaining mobile game, and when they are done with the game, they are rewarded with a coupon from one of Vrtii's partner brands or businesses. Once Vrtii users “win” a coupon, they have several options of what to do with it, including redeem it immediately, save it for later, exchange it for something else, or give it to a friend. And this is where where the Vrtii approach to advertising becomes truly revolutionary for advertisers: before users can redeem a coupon, they have to activate it, and advertisers only pay for the coupons that players activate. So unlike with other advertising platforms, where advertisements are a gamble and companies pay the same amount regardless of whether the coupon gets results, on Vrtii, advertisers only pay for coupons that are going to translate into real, meaningful customer interaction. And that's not the end of the value that our platform provides for businesses: our platform also provides powerful back-end tools that allow companies to monitor user behavior and response to their promotions, and give them the ability to target coupon delivery to specific audiences to maximize user engagement and effectiveness.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Apps, Commerce and Shopping, Gaming, Mobile, Platforms, Sales and Marketing, Software

Description: The Pyromaniac, LLC, is proud to announce the newest retail addition to the Connecticut shoreline.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Pyromaniac, LLC, is proud to announce  the newest retail addition to the Connecticut shoreline, bringing warmth, comfort and financial savings to homeowners of all types through efficient, green energy products and high end comfort solutions. A full Executive Summary, Business Plan and Private Placement Memorandum are available upon request.  The Pyromaniac, LLC  will provide top quality Hearth, Patio & Barbecue products and services to both residential and commercial accounts. The principal officer of The Pyromaniac, LLC  knows that many homeowners struggle with their home heating during the colder months, and often are forced to keep their homes much cooler than they would like, creating an uncomfortable living situation.  We believe in helping people to recapture and enjoy their homes during the cold months, as well as to further enjoy their homes outdoors during the warmer months. We believe in challenging the status quo of the standard, unorganized way that customers are served within the hearth industry, that they should be taken care of from start to finish with the homeowner’s risk reduced to zero.  However, most companies leave much of the risk on the homeowner, primarily by not previewing their home before the installation of their product. This often leads to incomplete jobs that are dragged on for days or weeks, increased cost to the homeowner, and inefficiencies within the business.
